WISDEM wind turbine ontology

Type: object

Ontology definition for wind turbines as defined in WP1 of IEA Wind Task 37 - Phase II

root comments
Type: string

Description of the model

root name
Type: string

Name of the turbine

root assembly
Type: object Default: {}

root assembly turbine_class
Type: enum (of integer or string) Default: "I"

IEC wind class of the wind turbine. The options are "I", "II", "III", and 'IV'

Must be one of:

  • "I"
  • "II"
  • "III"
  • "IV"
  • "i"
  • "ii"
  • "iii"
  • "iv"
  • 1
  • 2
  • 3
  • 4

root assembly turbulence_class
Type: enum (of string) Default: "B"

IEC turbulence class of the wind turbine. The options are "A", "B", and "C"

Must be one of:

  • "A"
  • "B"
  • "C"
  • "D"
  • "a"
  • "b"
  • "c"
  • "d"

root assembly drivetrain
Type: enum (of string) Default: "geared"

String characterizing the drivetrain configuration

Must be one of:

  • "Geared"
  • "geared"
  • "Direct_drive"
  • "Direct_Drive"
  • "Direct"
  • "direct_drive"
  • "direct"
  • "pm_direct_drive"
  • "Constant_eff"

root assembly rotor_orientation
Type: enum (of string) Default: "Upwind"

Orientation of the horizontal-axis rotor. The options are "Upwind" and "Downwind"

Must be one of:

  • "Upwind"
  • "upwind"
  • "UPWIND"
  • "downwind"
  • "Downwind"
  • "DOWNWIND"

root assembly number_of_blades
Type: integer Default: 3

Number of blades of the rotor

Value must be greater or equal to 0 and lesser or equal to 10

root assembly rotor_diameter
Type: number Default: 0

Diameter of the rotor, defined as two times the projected blade length plus the hub diameter

Value must be greater or equal to 0 and lesser or equal to 1000

root assembly hub_height
Type: number Default: 0

Height of the hub center over the ground (land-based) or the mean sea level (offshore)

Value must be greater or equal to 0 and lesser or equal to 1000

root assembly rated_power
Type: number

Nameplate power of the turbine, i.e. the rated electrical output of the generator.

Value must be greater or equal to 0

root assembly lifetime
Type: number Default: 25.0

Turbine design lifetime in years.

Value must be greater or equal to 0

root components blade outer_shape_bem reference_axis
Type: object

The reference system is used across wind turbine components. For the blade, the reference system is located at blade root, with z aligned with the pitch axis, x pointing towards the suction sides of the airfoils (standard prebend will be negative) and y pointing to the trailing edge (standard sweep will be positive). For tower and monopile, the reference system is located at tower/monopile base, with z aligned along the height pointing upwards, x aligned with the main wind direction, and y pointing to the side following the right hand rule.

For the blade, the reference system is located at blade root, with z aligned with the pitch axis, x pointing towards the suction sides of the airfoils (standard prebend will be negative) and y pointing to the trailing edge (standard sweep will be positive). For tower and monopile, the reference system is located at tower/monopile base, with z aligned along the height pointing upwards, x aligned with the main wind direction, and y pointing to the side following the right hand rule.

Same definition as reference_axis

The reference system is used across wind turbine components. For the blade, the reference system is located at blade root, with z aligned with the pitch axis, x pointing towards the suction sides of the airfoils (standard prebend will be negative) and y pointing to the trailing edge (standard sweep will be positive). For tower and monopile, the reference system is located at tower/monopile base, with z aligned along the height pointing upwards, x aligned with the main wind direction, and y pointing to the side following the right hand rule.
